{
  "text": "We observed no association between 25(OH)D concentrations and prevalent, early AMD assessed 3 years later in this community-based cohort of African Americans and Caucasians. These null associations were present regardless of age, sex, and race. Despite biological plausibility for a protective association between vitamin D status and AMD, associations between serum 25(OH)D and AMD across different study populations have been inconsistent. The body of literature, to date, consists of primarily cross sectional or casecontrol studies (2, 7-11, 13, 14, 33, 34) , with one retrospective cohort study of incident AMD cases [CITATION_1] .",
